<EventsDetail ID="x59043" Name="Opal Mining" Layout="general_activities.xsl"><Title type="string" label="Event Title" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Opal Mining</Title><Abstract type="string" label="Abstract" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Where are the seven dwarfs when you need them?</Abstract><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Event Details" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<p>Did you know that Idaho has Opal mines? That's right Opal mines. Just one hour away you can find the Spencer Opal Mines-- Idaho's largest Opal producer. On this fun trip we will be mining for precious stones. Is your favorite color white? Pink? Yellow? Blue? Well, Opal has all of those colors and more! Come join us on this geological adventure and bring a prize home with you.</p>
<p><br />Dates: June 30<br />Departure Time: 9 a.m.<br />Return Time: 2 p.m.<br />Cost: $10<br />Meeting location: ORC (under the North end of the stadium)</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Sign up at the ticket office or online at <strong> <a href="http://www.byui.edu/tickets">www.byui.edu/tickets</a></strong> </strong></p>
<p><strong> </strong></p>
<p><strong><strong>Contact: Scott Hurst</strong><br /><strong><a href="mailto:hursts@byui.edu">hursts@byui.edu</a> </strong></strong></p>
